description:
Lately, I’ve been hearing about using pea protein to make vegan versions of meat and eggs. So, when Sekaya, a Philippine national brand on wellness, came out with their pea protein powder, I knew I had to experiment with it for my vegan cooking. And here’s what I found out: it’s excellent for making vegan Tortang Talong! It tastes kind of eggy and meaty in this recipe. I’m happy to do this collab with them to show you how I was able to make vegan Tortang Talong.

For the full recipe, head to:  http://www.astigvegan.com/vegan-tortang-talong/
I wonder what else I can veganize using this pea protein 🤔 I’m excited to find out! 🔍

Thank you Sekaya for sponsoring this post! 🎉
